00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:47,470
A second-hand car.

570
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:49,200
He didn't say he won't pay us.

571
00:20:49,230 --> 00:20:50,990
Don't bother me about this.

572
00:20:50,990 --> 00:20:52,150
Wait.

573
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:54,350
It's cold. I'll heat it up for you.

574
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:01,990
Ask him to write a guarantee.

575
00:21:01,990 --> 00:21:03,350
Make it clear when he'd pay us back.

576
00:21:03,390 --> 00:21:04,230
If he doesn't do so by the deadline,

577
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:05,270
he has to pay a late fee.

578
00:21:05,270 --> 00:21:06,230
Are you crazy?

579
00:21:07,390 --> 00:21:08,620
Our business

580
00:21:08,910 --> 00:21:10,670
were all from him.

581
00:21:11,150 --> 00:21:12,270
If we offend him,

582
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:14,430
we are left with nothing.

583
00:21:14,450 --> 00:21:15,610
You are the crazy one instead.

584
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:17,550
You are working for him for free.

585
00:21:17,870 --> 00:21:19,550
What are you getting out of it?

586
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:21,000
-You’re the crazy one instead!
-Okay, okay.

587
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,430
Stay out of men's business.

588
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,230
How can I not care?

589
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:26,150
Let me tell you.

590
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:27,790
In the past when we did seafaring,

591
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:29,950
yes, we could accept late payments.

592
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:30,620
We could still hold things up.

593
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:31,790
But not anymore.

594
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:32,550
If he doesn't pay us now,

595
00:21:32,550 --> 00:21:34,370
how are we going to get by?

596
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,000
What are you talking about?

597
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:38,550
H-Have I ever mistreated you two?

598
00:21:56,770 --> 00:21:57,750
Where are you going?

599
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:17,880
What's your family arguing about?

600
00:22:19,430 --> 00:22:20,530
Money.

601
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:21,550
What else could it be?

602
00:22:27,590 --> 00:22:29,460
If I get married,

603
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,200
it doesn't matter if he has money or not.

604
00:22:32,230 --> 00:22:33,800
He must not be too filial.

605
00:22:35,230 --> 00:22:35,920
Why?

606
00:22:36,710 --> 00:22:38,670
The money he worked hard for

607
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,190
will all end up with his mother.

608
00:22:40,190 --> 00:22:41,150
What's left for the family?

609
00:22:41,710 --> 00:22:42,910
Find someone rich.

610
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:44,920
He can then satisfy both sides.

611
00:22:50,670 --> 00:22:51,470
What?

612
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:54,470
If you become rich in the future...

613
00:22:54,990 --> 00:22:56,560
If I become rich,

614
00:22:57,430 --> 00:22:59,150
I'll buy my dad's boat

615
00:22:59,470 --> 00:23:00,540
and force him to retire.

616
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:01,950
Then,

617
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,230
I'll buy them a big house in the city,

618
00:23:04,230 --> 00:23:05,310
the kind with a garden.

619
00:23:05,890 --> 00:23:07,460
They can then

620
00:23:08,070 --> 00:23:09,020
watch birds,

621
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:10,090
do some gardening,

622
00:23:10,310 --> 00:23:11,110
and sunbathe all at home

623
00:23:11,150 --> 00:23:11,990
with no worries.

624
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:13,670
That's boring.

625
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:14,870
They will be bored to death.

626
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:17,980
You...

627
00:23:18,890 --> 00:23:21,140
don't know how lucky you are.

628
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:23,630
You're oblivious to your parents' hard work.

629
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:30,010
The canal is hopeless.

630
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:32,650
You can't make a living with seafaring anymore.

631
00:23:33,110 --> 00:23:34,370
I think those on Flower Street

632
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:35,790
won't last that much longer either.

633
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:38,910
If you move the tree, it dies.

634
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:39,990
If people move, we live.

635
00:23:40,470 --> 00:23:41,430
From now on,

636
00:23:41,430 --> 00:23:43,630
we'll go wherever there's good prospects.

637
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:45,020
As long as we work hard,

638
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,300
we won't starve to death.

639
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:48,590
Where do you want to go the most?

640
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,680
I don't know still.

641
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:53,680
What about you?

642
00:23:56,710 --> 00:23:57,630
Beijing.

643
00:23:58,150 --> 00:23:59,030
Zhongguancun.

644
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,410
I'll go when I grow up.

645
00:24:03,510 --> 00:24:04,710
How old is old enough?

646
00:24:06,990 --> 00:24:08,730
At least after we graduate from high school.

647
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:10,710
Regardless,

648
00:24:11,470 --> 00:24:12,870
I am not going to

649
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:14,430
sit here and wait for death.

650
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:22,100
[Rejected]

651
00:24:19,230 --> 00:24:21,760
According to "Stories to Awaken the World",

652
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:24,670
Du Shiniang and Li Jia

653
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:27,630
boarded the ship from Chongwen Gate of Beijing.

654
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:30,630
There's no Yangtze River in Beijing.

655
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,230
It's clearly just a canal.

656
00:24:35,150 --> 00:24:36,630
After they came to Guazhou,

657
00:24:36,630 --> 00:24:37,390
they were met with a blizzard.

658
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:40,070
They haven't had the chance to transfer to Yangtze River.

659
00:24:40,070 --> 00:24:42,030
How could this treasure box

660
00:24:42,030 --> 00:24:44,480
then sink in the Yangtze River?

661
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:47,310
It's because Feng Menglong

662
00:24:47,310 --> 00:24:50,870
used the word "river" to replace the canal.

663
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:53,030
So,

664
00:24:53,870 --> 00:24:55,230
the treasure box

665
00:24:55,230 --> 00:24:57,710
should have sunken in the canal.

666
00:24:56,940 --> 00:25:00,300
[Heaven rewards the diligent]

667
00:24:57,710 --> 00:25:00,160
There is nothing wrong about this.

668
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:12,750
[Heaven rewards the diligent]

669
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:09,710
My manuscripts

670
00:25:10,670 --> 00:25:12,460
have been rejected before.

671
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:14,990
But previously when the manuscript was rejected...

672
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:17,370
Lift up your leg.

673
00:25:17,470 --> 00:25:18,990
At least they would write

674
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:20,990
why they rejected the manuscript.

675
00:25:21,710 --> 00:25:23,990
They would make clear of the reason.

676
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:26,300
But now,

677
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:28,110
they can't even be bothered to write a single word.

678
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:30,910
It's returned simply with a stamp,

679
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:33,030
and they even returned it to my company.

680
00:25:33,390 --> 00:25:34,450
Let me ask you.

681
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:36,230
You read it too.

682
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:37,830
Why did they reject my manuscript?

683
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,000
What grounds do they have?

684
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:39,790
Enough.

685
00:25:39,790 --> 00:25:41,200
Why are you yelling at him?

686
00:25:41,230 --> 00:25:42,630
He's not from the publisher.

687
00:25:42,630 --> 00:25:44,350
I can't stand it!

688
00:25:44,470 --> 00:25:45,610
If you can't,

689
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,390
just treat it like a fart.

690
00:25:47,390 --> 00:25:48,870
What are you talking about?

691
00:25:48,870 --> 00:25:49,900
How can you say that?

692
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:50,440
Dad.

693
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,200
Calm down.

694
00:25:52,780 --> 00:25:54,450
I-I read the manuscript just now.

695
00:25:54,620 --> 00:25:55,910
I-I think...

696
00:25:56,270 --> 00:25:57,110
it's not that you were rejected

697
00:25:58,430 --> 00:26:00,500
because you are not skilled enough.

698
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:07,830
Let me ask you.

699
00:26:09,260 --> 00:26:11,870
So, why did they reject my manuscript?

700
00:26:16,470 --> 00:26:19,820
I-I think it's the theme.

701
00:26:21,150 --> 00:26:22,500
Theme?

702
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:24,570
What do you mean?

703
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,870
That Du Shiniang

704
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:29,410
are all outdated stories of the past.

705
00:26:29,420 --> 00:26:31,090
Nowadays, readers are not interested in that.

706
00:26:31,170 --> 00:26:32,780
It's not easy to read or sell.

707
00:26:37,620 --> 00:26:40,190
So what are they interested in?

708
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:41,320
This year,

709
00:26:41,470 --> 00:26:43,830
the best-selling novel is called "Ghost Blows Out the Light".

710
00:26:43,990 --> 00:26:45,070
It's centered around tomb raiding.

711
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:46,710
With your skills, I am sure

712
00:26:46,710 --> 00:26:47,750
you can write better stories with your eyes closed.

713
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:49,310
What are you talking about?

714
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:50,310
What are you doing?

715
00:26:50,470 --> 00:26:51,950
How could you hit him?

716
00:26:51,950 --> 00:26:52,430
Are you okay?

717
00:26:52,430 --> 00:26:54,060
How could he say that?

718
00:26:54,390 --> 00:26:56,140
He asked me to write about tomb raiders.

719
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:58,390
Why don't he ask me to write about murder and arson?

720
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,430
That works too.

721
00:26:59,430 --> 00:27:01,150
A story on a psychopathic killer who does serial killings would also sell.

722
00:27:01,150 --> 00:27:01,710
Get out!

723
00:27:01,710 --> 00:27:02,900
How inappropriate!

724
00:27:02,950 --> 00:27:04,730
I'm a scholar!

725
00:27:05,230 --> 00:27:07,910
How can I write about crap like that?

726
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:09,940
I have my integrity

727
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:12,690
and morals, you know?

728
00:27:14,910 --> 00:27:15,710
Calm down.

729
00:27:15,710 --> 00:27:17,030
How does he take after me?

730
00:27:17,030 --> 00:27:18,190
All right.

731
00:27:24,930 --> 00:27:27,480
When those literary artists write, they go...

732
00:27:29,660 --> 00:27:32,100
No, Grandpa, why don't you actually write something?

733
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:32,760
I want to see.

734
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:33,310
I...

735
00:27:33,310 --> 00:27:35,230
I don't write well either.

736
00:27:35,230 --> 00:27:36,190
I told you to practice hard.

737
00:27:36,190 --> 00:27:37,670
Practice hard until you are like a calligrapher.

738
00:27:40,310 --> 00:27:41,740
You have to know how to leave even spaces.

739
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,310
You mean to leave room for error, right?

740
00:27:43,310 --> 00:27:43,950
Yes.

741
00:27:45,510 --> 00:27:46,870
You just want me to stay at home

742
00:27:46,910 --> 00:27:48,390
and be a housewife, don't you?

743
00:27:48,390 --> 00:27:49,470
That's not what I mean.

744
00:27:49,470 --> 00:27:50,670
That's what you meant.

745
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:52,210
All these years,

746
00:27:52,550 --> 00:27:53,530
I've been

747
00:27:53,670 --> 00:27:54,630
supporting this household

748
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,120
and contributing to our family.

749
00:27:56,310 --> 00:27:57,710
I don't ask for your understanding

750
00:27:57,710 --> 00:27:59,260
nor for you to be grateful.

751
00:27:59,980 --> 00:28:00,750
But now,

752
00:28:01,750 --> 00:28:03,390
I just want to get back what I've lost

753
00:28:03,430 --> 00:28:04,970
bit by bit.

754
00:28:05,230 --> 00:28:06,450
What did you lose?

755
00:28:06,710 --> 00:28:08,110
My old name

756
00:28:08,150 --> 00:28:09,920
was Luo Zhimei.

757
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:11,160
But now?

758
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:13,150
Who knows my name now?

759
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:16,040
Everyone calls me Haikuo's mother.

760
00:28:16,190 --> 00:28:17,600
As the days go by,

761
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,470
I've lost my name.

762
00:28:20,470 --> 00:28:21,150
Zhimei.

763
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,070
They call you Haikuo's mom because

764
00:28:23,070 --> 00:28:25,230
that's how they've been addressing each other.

765
00:28:25,910 --> 00:28:27,150
Of course your name is Luo Zhimei.

766
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:29,150
You are always Luo Zhimei in my heart.

767
00:28:29,150 --> 00:28:30,090
Besides,

768
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:31,590
can you get your name back

769
00:28:31,630 --> 00:28:32,870
by just acting in a small role?

770
00:28:32,870 --> 00:28:34,190
At least in the ending credits,

771
00:28:34,190 --> 00:28:36,230
the words "Luo Zhimei" will appear on the screen.

772
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:37,630
There are only ads at the end of the film.

773
00:28:37,630 --> 00:28:38,390
There are no ending credits.

774
00:28:38,390 --> 00:28:39,750
Stop being unreasonable.

775
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:41,570
I'm telling you, Zhou Yanlin.

776
00:28:41,950 --> 00:28:42,870
This time,

777
00:28:42,870 --> 00:28:43,550
I'm definitely leaving.

778
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:45,020
Don't try to stop me.

779
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:51,740
It's not like I won't let you go.

780
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:58,470
Right now, it's inappropriate whether or not

781
00:28:58,470 --> 00:28:59,470
I say something or say nothing.

782
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:00,780
I'll just get scolded anyway.

783
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:01,880
What can I do?

784
00:29:01,910 --> 00:29:03,470
Your dad treats you well.

785
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:04,310
Not at all.

786
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,550
♫When the moon hangs in the sky♫

787
00:29:15,830 --> 00:29:16,850
You're all here.

788
00:29:17,670 --> 00:29:19,470
So, what's your family arguing about?

789
00:29:17,790 --> 00:29:19,550
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

790
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:22,860
♫Who is still by your side?♫

791
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,710
My mom wants to go to Hengdian.

792
00:29:23,740 --> 00:29:25,110
My dad doesn't agree.

793
00:29:24,530 --> 00:29:28,260
♫As time passes♫

794
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:26,090
Why not?

795
00:29:27,710 --> 00:29:30,470
Maybe he's worried.

796
00:29:29,170 --> 00:29:32,950
♫Is a lifetime really that long?♫

797
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:33,530
He's afraid my mom won't come back after becoming a star.

798
00:29:33,570 --> 00:29:36,710
Your mom becoming a star? Your dad thinks too much.

799
00:29:36,390 --> 00:29:39,930
♫When youthful company fades, leaving only small talk and pleasantries♫

800
00:29:40,230 --> 00:29:41,740
If it weren't for me,

801
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:44,020
♫Spring feels short, while autumn lingers♫

802
00:29:41,740 --> 00:29:43,870
my mom would have succeeded by now.

803
00:29:45,510 --> 00:29:47,110
I guess my mom resented me.

804
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:49,670
♫A gentle breeze carries dreams away♫

805
00:29:49,610 --> 00:29:51,140
My mom also resented me.

806
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:54,050
♫Of sweet dreams♫

807
00:29:51,770 --> 00:29:52,560
Why?

808
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:57,030
Both my dad and my grandma wanted to have a boy.

809
00:29:57,490 --> 00:29:58,880
But they had a daughter instead.

810
00:29:59,150 --> 00:30:02,160
♫Life is long♫

811
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:01,350
That's why my mum can't hold her head up for the rest of her life.

812
00:30:03,630 --> 00:30:06,800
♫No need to dwell♫

813
00:30:03,780 --> 00:30:06,090
That's all in the past.

814
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:08,030
Why are they still arguing today?

815
00:30:07,950 --> 00:30:11,470
♫Like moonlight♫

816
00:30:08,790 --> 00:30:10,230
When they made good money a few years ago,

817
00:30:10,950 --> 00:30:12,470
we didn't feel like life was tough.

818
00:30:12,780 --> 00:30:16,380
♫Don't forget♫

819
00:30:13,150 --> 00:30:14,470
Now that they're short of money,

820
00:30:15,310 --> 00:30:16,870
they couldn't control their temper anymore.

821
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:20,460
♫Life is long♫

822
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:24,920
♫No need to dwell♫

823
00:30:26,970 --> 00:30:30,280
♫Like moonlight♫

824
00:30:29,150 --> 00:30:30,700
So

825
00:30:31,890 --> 00:30:35,450
♫The old times♫

826
00:30:31,990 --> 00:30:33,880
we all have to push forward.

827
00:30:34,060 --> 00:30:35,790
Now that our families are not doing well,

828
00:30:35,790 --> 00:30:37,930
they are going to rely on us.

829
00:30:38,510 --> 00:30:39,610
With money,

830
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:41,410
my mom won't be mad at my dad

831
00:30:41,430 --> 00:30:42,910
for not getting the payments.

832
00:30:42,940 --> 00:30:44,730
Haikuo's mom wouldn't be in a hurry

833
00:30:44,810 --> 00:30:46,030
to go out and act.

834
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:47,070
Fenghua's family?

835
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:48,620
If they really wanted a son,

836
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,280
they could just have one.

837
00:30:50,780 --> 00:30:53,830
So in the end, it's all because of money.

838
00:30:54,110 --> 00:30:55,010
I agree.

839
00:30:55,470 --> 00:30:56,580
Once I graduate,

840
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:57,980
I will go to Lanzhou.

841
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:59,840
♫Life is long♫

842
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,350
Lanzhou? You want to learn how to make noodles?

843
00:31:01,270 --> 00:31:04,290
♫No need to dwell♫

844
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:05,930
We see the people of the canal every day when we open our eyes,

845
00:31:05,740 --> 00:31:08,990
♫Like moonlight♫

846
00:31:06,510 --> 00:31:09,040
whose fates are also intertwined with the canal.

